column13: the URI in the Location header returns a status of 204 on success. If the asynchronous request failed
column14: the URI in the Location header returns an error-level status code.']

samples: [u"Upgrades the operating system of the specified pool.  During an upgrade
column11: the Batch service upgrades each compute node in the pool. When a compute node is chosen for upgrade
column12: any tasks running on that node are removed from the node and returned to the queue to be rerun later (or on a different compute node). The node will be unavailable until the upgrade is complete. This operation results in temporarily reduced pool capacity as nodes are taken out of service to be upgraded. Although the Batch service tries to avoid upgrading all compute nodes at the same time
column13: it does not guarantee to do this (particularly on small pools); therefore
column14: the pool may be temporarily unavailable to run tasks. When this operation runs
column15: the pool state changes to upgrading. When all compute nodes have finished upgrading
column16: the pool state returns to active. While the upgrade is in progress
column17: the pool's currentOSVersion reflects the OS version that nodes are upgrading from
column18: and targetOSVersion reflects the OS version that nodes are upgrading to. Once the upgrade is complete
column19: currentOSVersion is updated to reflect the OS version now running on all nodes. This operation can only be invoked on pools created with the cloudServiceConfiguration property."]

column13: or a page blob. If the destination blob already exists
column14: it must be of the  same blob type as the source blob. Any existing destination blob will be  overwritten. The destination blob cannot be modified while a copy operation  is in progress.  When copying from a page blob

column16: initially containing all zeroes. Then  the source page ranges are enumerated

column19: all committed blocks and their block IDs are copied.  Uncommitted blocks are not copied. At the end of the copy operation
column20: the  destination blob will have the same committed block count as the source.  When copying from an append blob
column21: all committed blocks are copied. At the  end of the copy operation
column22: the destination blob will have the same committed  block count as the source.  For all blob types
column23: you can call get_blob_properties on the destination  blob to check the status of the copy operation. The final blob will be  committed when the copy completes."

column11: the following actions occur: the pool state is set to deleting; any ongoing resize operation on the pool are stopped; the Batch service starts resizing the pool to zero nodes; any tasks running on existing nodes are terminated and requeued (as if a resize pool operation had been requested with the default requeue option); finally
column12: the pool is removed from the system. Because running tasks are requeued
column13: the user can rerun these tasks by updating their job to target a different pool. The tasks can then run on the new pool. If you want to override the requeue behavior
column14: then you should call resize pool explicitly to shrink the pool to zero size before deleting the pool. If you call an Update
column15: Patch or Delete API on a pool in the deleting state
column16: it will fail with HTTP status code 409 with error code PoolBeingDeleted.']

samples: [u"Upgrades the operating system of the specified pool.  During an upgrade
column11: the Batch service upgrades each compute node in the pool. When a compute node is chosen for upgrade
column12: any tasks running on that node are removed from the node and returned to the queue to be rerun later (or on a different compute node). The node will be unavailable until the upgrade is complete. This operation results in temporarily reduced pool capacity as nodes are taken out of service to be upgraded. Although the Batch service tries to avoid upgrading all compute nodes at the same time
column13: it does not guarantee to do this (particularly on small pools); therefore
column14: the pool may be temporarily unavailable to run tasks. When this operation runs
column15: the pool state changes to upgrading. When all compute nodes have finished upgrading
column16: the pool state returns to active. While the upgrade is in progress
column17: the pool's currentOSVersion reflects the OS version that nodes are upgrading from
column18: and targetOSVersion reflects the OS version that nodes are upgrading to. Once the upgrade is complete
column19: currentOSVersion is updated to reflect the OS version now running on all nodes. This operation can only be invoked on pools created with the cloudServiceConfiguration property."]

column19: initially containing all zeroes. Then  the source page ranges are enumerated

column22: all committed blocks and their block IDs are copied.  Uncommitted blocks are not copied. At the end of the copy operation

column24: all committed blocks are copied. At the  end of the copy operation

column13: u"Upgrades the operating system of the specified pool.  During an upgrade
column14: the Batch service upgrades each compute node in the pool. When a compute node is chosen for upgrade
column15: any tasks running on that node are removed from the node and returned to the queue to be rerun later (or on a different compute node). The node will be unavailable until the upgrade is complete. This operation results in temporarily reduced pool capacity as nodes are taken out of service to be upgraded. Although the Batch service tries to avoid upgrading all compute nodes at the same time
column16: it does not guarantee to do this (particularly on small pools); therefore
column17: the pool may be temporarily unavailable to run tasks. When this operation runs
column18: the pool state changes to upgrading. When all compute nodes have finished upgrading
column19: the pool state returns to active. While the upgrade is in progress
column20: the pool's currentOSVersion reflects the OS version that nodes are upgrading from
column21: and targetOSVersion reflects the OS version that nodes are upgrading to. Once the upgrade is complete
column22: currentOSVersion is updated to reflect the OS version now running on all nodes. This operation can only be invoked on pools created with the cloudServiceConfiguration property."]
